Interface WorldCursorProvider

  • All Superinterfaces:
    MapProvider
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultPlayerCursorProvider

    public interface WorldCursorProvider
extends MapProvider
    Provides a Minimap with WorldCursor that will appear on the canvas, may be called extremely frequently(Several times per tick).
    Author:
    BananaPuncher714

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Get a collection of WorldCursor that will be placed on the map.

    • Method Detail

      • getCursors

        java.util.Collection<WorldCursor> getCursors(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                                             Minimap map,
                                             PlayerSetting setting)
        Get a collection of WorldCursor that will be placed on the map. To place cursors relative to the map canvas, use a MapCursorProvider.
        Parameters:
        player - The player for who this is rendering. Do not use the location of this player, may not be accurate.
        map - The Minimap which is requesting the cursors.
        setting - The PlayerSetting of the player, including the location of the player that will be used to render the canvas.
        Returns:
        A collection of WorldCursor. Can return null.
